How to use?
- Download and extract replace.app.zip.

- Get the uber cool alternative sublimetext icon from here:
  https://github.com/dmatarazzo/Sublime-Text-2-Icon

  Alternatively, here's yet another cool icon:
  http://www.sublimetext.com/forum/download/file.php?id=200

- Put the downloaded icon in the same directory of replace.app. (File name of the icon has to be "Sublime Text 2.icns".)

- Run replace.app
